              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target  consists of a 45x70 mm**2, self-supporting",
                " metallic natural lithium foil  (92.5%  7Li  and  7.5%",
                " 6Li), 100 or 50 micron thick (depending on the photon",
                " energy)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SILI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Seven  silicon  strip  detectors.",
                "The distance  from  the  detector to the center of the",
                " target was 17 cm,  with full detector (all 16 strips)",
                " solid   angle   of  0.09  sr.  the  detector  angular",
                " acceptance (for a point target) was +- 8.4 degree."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Direct measurements.",
                "At Eg  = 6.56 MeV sum 20%  of intensity is distributed",
                " among several low intensity lines.",
                "At Eg  =  8.8  MeV sum 25% of intensity is distributed",
                " among several low intensity lines.",
                "The background  from  the  reaction  n  + 6Li -> t + a",
                " caused by neutrons from both beam  contamination  and",
                " background in the experimental area was evaluated and",
                " subtracted."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Mean-root-square   errors.    Bands    were",
                " obtained by  reconstructing  the  differential  cross",
                " sections from the published Legendre coefficients."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Measured  angular  distributions  were  normalized  to",
                " unity at the angle = 90 deg."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Angular distributions   of   tritons  emitted  in  the",
                " reaction 7Li(g,t)a have been measured for two  photon",
                " energy  intervals (6.4 - 6.7 and 8.5 - 9.0 MeV),  and",
                " theta-t between 30 and 150 deg. Monochromatic photons",
                " from  neutron  capture  reactions of the IPEN/CNEN-SP",
                " IEA-R1 research reactor were used.  The measured data",
                " were  analyzed in  the  framework of an alpha-cluster",
                " model  for  the  7Li  structure.  Results are in good",
                " agreement with a recent measurement  of the azimuthal",
                " cross section asymmetry."
              ]
            }
          ],
